More arrests overnight and this morning at the Beitbridge border post. People were trying to get into South Africa illegally. Meanwhile, the Home Affairs Portfolio Committee has visited the Lebombo border post on Thursday. Aviwe Mtila has the latest at the Lebombo border post and Slindelo Masikane is at Beitbridge. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police have made more arrests at the Beitbridge border post. People were trying to get into South Africa illegally. READ: SA Lockdown: Dozens arrested at Mozambique border post Meanwhile, the Home Affairs Portfolio Committee has visited the Lebombo border post on Wednesday. Twenty land ports of entry are closed as lockdown level 3 continues. Earlier this week police arrested about 80 people who were trying to enter the country illegally at the Lebombo border post.